### Sync API
### Base URL: /api/v1/sync/

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api/v1

### Check current content version (lightweight staleness check)
# Returns {"version": "<ISO-8601>"} or {"version": null} if no published lessons.
# Client calls this on app launch — only syncs if version differs from local.
GET {{baseUrl}}/sync/version/ HTTP/1.1

###

### Full sync — all published lessons and courses
# Returns: version, lesson_uuids, lessons[], course_uuids, courses[]
# lesson_uuids / course_uuids always contain the full published set
# so the client can prune locally deleted content.
GET {{baseUrl}}/sync/lessons/ HTTP/1.1

###

### Delta sync — only lessons updated after a given timestamp
# Replace the timestamp with the version value stored after the last full sync.
# lessons[] contains only changed lessons; lesson_uuids, courses[], and course_lessons[]
# always contain the full published set regardless of `since`.
GET {{baseUrl}}/sync/lessons/?since=2026-01-01T00:00:00Z HTTP/1.1

###

### Delta sync — naive datetime (no timezone suffix)
# Server treats naive ISO-8601 as UTC.
GET {{baseUrl}}/sync/lessons/?since=2026-01-01T00:00:00 HTTP/1.1

###

### Delta sync — far-future cutoff (expects empty lessons list)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sync/lessons/?since=2099-12-31T23:59:59Z HTTP/1.1

###

### Invalid since value (expects 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sync/lessons/?since=not-a-date HTTP/1.1
